Package: dupglobals
Title: Regression: Duplicate File-Scope Global Names Across Files
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Test", "Author", email = "test@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Regression fixture for two .c files declaring file-scope
    globals named "scan" with different struct types. Mirrors what
    utf8 has across check_wordscan.c and check_graphscan.c. The runner
    treats duplicate plain Definition globals as per-file internals so
    the package no longer crashes with "Top-level mutable variable has
    an incompatible type."
